while you were gone.

558
00:44:19,038 --> 00:44:20,031
She's angry at me a lot too.

559
00:44:20,116 --> 00:44:20,986
Hey!

560
00:44:21,238 --> 00:44:22,738
When did I ever bully you?

561
00:44:22,823 --> 00:44:23,664
See?

562
00:44:23,749 --> 00:44:25,285
She yelled and swore at me.

563
00:44:25,384 --> 00:44:27,844
I swear. It was hell without you.

564
00:44:28,734 --> 00:44:30,219
He needs a good beating.

565
00:44:30,308 --> 00:44:31,691
I've been too nice to you lately.

566
00:44:31,776 --> 00:44:34,142
Come here you. Come here.

567
00:44:36,053 --> 00:44:37,180
You deserve to be beaten.

568
00:44:37,265 --> 00:44:40,545
You deserve it for saying
stupid things like that.

569
00:44:41,447 --> 00:44:42,452
See?

570
00:44:42,705 --> 00:44:44,844
She hits and abuses me.

571
00:44:45,083 --> 00:44:48,544
I hate Yoo Woomi the most.

572
00:44:49,292 --> 00:44:50,561
You're all I have.

573
00:44:51,424 --> 00:44:53,175
I finally feel like I'm back.

574
00:44:53,266 --> 00:44:54,939
You lost so much weight.

575
00:44:55,265 --> 00:44:58,193
I was able to survive
thanks to your mom's side dishes.

576
00:44:58,853 --> 00:45:00,599
Please thank her for me.

577
00:45:00,700 --> 00:45:02,023
You tell her yourself.

578
00:45:02,192 --> 00:45:04,032
My mom misses you so much.

579
00:45:04,117 --> 00:45:07,489
She's sad she has no one
to play Go-Stop with.

580
00:45:07,573 --> 00:45:09,778
I better go there and
make her lose some money.

581
00:45:09,863 --> 00:45:10,734
Hey!

582
00:45:11,259 --> 00:45:13,755
What should we do after we unpacked?

583
00:45:14,783 --> 00:45:16,574
It's been a while, so why don't
we have a drinking party?

584
00:45:16,659 --> 00:45:17,407
Okay?

585
00:45:17,491 --> 00:45:19,192
No. I have somewhere to be.

586
00:45:19,310 --> 00:45:20,282
Did you hear that?

587
00:45:20,367 --> 00:45:23,589
He does that all the time
ever since he started dating.

588
00:45:24,198 --> 00:45:26,267
You traitor!

589
00:45:27,247 --> 00:45:29,789
-It's just the two of us then...
-Sorry.

590
00:45:30,147 --> 00:45:31,506
I need to go somewhere too.

591
00:45:32,340 --> 00:45:34,014
Look at you two.

592
00:45:35,272 --> 00:45:37,129
Do you think I don't have
anyone to hang out with?

593
00:45:37,521 --> 00:45:39,061
I have somewhere to be as well, okay?

594
00:45:41,577 --> 00:45:42,587
Geez.

595
00:45:44,359 --> 00:45:45,969
Hi, honey...

596
00:45:46,103 --> 00:45:47,293
It's me.

597
00:45:47,528 --> 00:45:48,880
Are you busy later?

598
00:45:50,027 --> 00:45:51,079
You are?

599
00:45:51,164 --> 00:45:52,947
-Geez.
-Are you sure?

600
00:45:53,031 --> 00:45:54,984
-Anyway, what about that room?
-What?

601
00:45:55,069 --> 00:45:56,982
What happened to that room
with the framed photos?

602
00:45:57,067 --> 00:45:58,303
It was empty.

603
00:46:19,660 --> 00:46:21,373
I was planning to go pick you up.

604
00:46:23,560 --> 00:46:25,620
I thought you would,
so I came here instead.

605
00:46:32,446 --> 00:46:34,240
I've always only been receiving them.

606
00:46:36,012 --> 00:46:37,821
I don't know how to react to this.

607
00:46:38,018 --> 00:46:39,557
It's the first time
I've ever received flowers.

608
00:46:39,668 --> 00:46:41,612
As someone who has received
countless of them...

609
00:46:41,696 --> 00:46:42,987
...it's not really a big deal.

610
00:46:43,376 --> 00:46:45,693
Just receive them with a big smile.

611
00:46:47,048 --> 00:46:49,481
You sure know how to drive me crazy.

612
00:46:54,224 --> 00:46:55,124
I...

613
00:46:55,708 --> 00:46:56,977
...became the CEO.

614
00:46:57,896 --> 00:46:59,313
Today is my first day...

615
00:46:59,619 --> 00:47:00,746
...as the CEO.

616
00:47:01,126 --> 00:47:01,987
Really?

617
00:47:02,630 --> 00:47:04,630
Good thing I bought the flowers.

618
00:47:06,006 --> 00:47:07,735
What do you want as a gift?

619
00:47:15,420 --> 00:47:16,594
Do you want to go eat some ramyun?

620
00:47:16,848 --> 00:47:17,856
At my home.

621
00:47:59,265 --> 00:48:00,559
The photos...

622
00:48:01,702 --> 00:48:02,963
...are all here.

623
00:48:04,340 --> 00:48:05,816
After you disappeared...

624
00:48:07,080 --> 00:48:09,654
...I want to at least
keep one picture of you.

625
00:48:11,058 --> 00:48:13,876
But I didn't know
which one was the real you.

626
00:48:15,321 --> 00:48:16,896
But then it hit me...

627
00:48:18,017 --> 00:48:19,339
...they are all you.

628
00:48:21,415 --> 00:48:22,251
So I took them all.

629
00:48:29,320 --> 00:48:30,268
Then...

630
00:48:32,188 --> 00:48:33,410
...you've seen all of them.

631
00:48:34,565 --> 00:48:35,743
My faces.

632
00:48:36,536 --> 00:48:37,617
Yes, I did.

633
00:48:39,983 --> 00:48:41,586
I was happy...

634
00:48:42,408 --> 00:48:43,680
...that I could see all of them.

635
00:48:45,833 --> 00:48:47,073
It'll probably...

636
00:48:48,257 --> 00:48:50,057
...be harder from now on.

637
00:48:51,075 --> 00:48:54,850
You can recognize the real me now.

638
00:48:59,800 --> 00:49:01,918
I seem to only make you suffer.

639
00:49:02,914 --> 00:49:04,090
Don't worry.

640
00:49:04,558 --> 00:49:07,156
I'm not in love with
what's on the outside.

641
00:49:12,847 --> 00:49:13,696
But...

642
00:49:17,043 --> 00:49:18,087
...I'm in love...

643
00:49:19,374 --> 00:49:20,514
...with what's inside.

644
00:49:25,142 --> 00:49:28,027
How can an amazing person
like you come into my life?

645
00:49:29,197 --> 00:49:30,054
No.

646
00:49:31,915 --> 00:49:33,644
It's you who came to me.

647
00:49:35,106 --> 00:49:36,572
You're the one...

648
00:49:37,593 --> 00:49:38,556
...who came into my life.

649
00:49:47,751 --> 00:49:49,799
(Those Who Read Books to You)

650
00:49:54,457 --> 00:49:55,789
How did you know?

651
00:49:55,873 --> 00:49:57,072
That I'm doing this?

652
00:49:57,404 --> 00:49:58,283
Well...

653
00:49:59,621 --> 00:50:01,919
Woomi might have been your friend,

654
00:50:02,125 --> 00:50:03,904
but she's also my friend now.

655
00:50:04,718 --> 00:50:06,276
And Eunho is like a younger brother to me.

656
00:50:07,337 --> 00:50:09,237
Once they befriend someone...

657
00:50:09,553 --> 00:50:11,980
...they tend to be loyal till the end.

658
00:50:12,065 --> 00:50:13,319
You're right.

659
00:50:14,932 --> 00:50:17,774
I listen to this
every time I miss hearing your voice.

660
00:50:18,525 --> 00:50:21,717
I think I wrote about 30 comments.

661
00:50:24,199 --> 00:50:26,001
Anyway, when you invited
me over for some ramyun,

662
00:50:26,086 --> 00:50:28,064
I didn't know you meant it literally.

663
00:50:29,094 --> 00:50:29,994
What?

664
00:50:30,371 --> 00:50:31,782
Were you expecting something else?

665
00:50:32,987 --> 00:50:33,997
Not really.

666
00:50:35,031 --> 00:50:37,839
That's exactly what
lustful eyes looked like.

667
00:50:38,923 --> 00:50:40,066
You're totally wrong.

668
00:50:40,151 --> 00:50:42,086
Then, you should have been more subtle.

669
00:50:42,170 --> 00:50:43,803
Gosh. I told you, you're wrong.

670
00:50:43,887 --> 00:50:45,887
Gosh. I'm totally right.

671
00:50:51,005 --> 00:50:52,226
The ramyun was good.

672
00:50:54,358 --> 00:50:57,070
You're really good at making ramyun.

673
00:50:57,155 --> 00:50:58,446
You should spend the night here.

674
00:51:01,161 --> 00:51:02,668
Why? You don't want to?

675
00:51:02,753 --> 00:51:05,166
Why would you suddenly say that
while eating ramyun?

676
00:51:05,251 --> 00:51:07,885
Are there steps to say that or something?

677
00:51:08,370 --> 00:51:09,972
I thought you said it's all about timing.

678
00:51:14,419 --> 00:51:16,868
Anyway, there's something
I've been curious about.

679
00:51:20,098 --> 00:51:21,555
What's that about?

680
00:51:25,747 --> 00:51:26,890
Can't you tell?

681
00:51:27,373 --> 00:51:28,481
She's my girlfriend.

682
00:51:29,682 --> 00:51:31,715
How's that your girlfriend?
It should be me.

683
00:51:36,436 --> 00:51:37,763
I have a wish.

684
00:51:38,430 --> 00:51:39,347
A wish?

685
00:51:39,900 --> 00:51:40,840
What is it?

686
00:51:41,222 --> 00:51:43,287
Tell me. I'll grant you anything.

687
00:51:43,724 --> 00:51:44,994
I want to watch a movie.

688
00:51:45,457 --> 00:51:46,470
One you starred in.

689
00:51:46,581 --> 00:51:47,444
A movie?

690
00:51:48,290 --> 00:51:49,135
Again?

691
00:51:49,676 --> 00:51:50,829
Sure. Let's watch it.

692
00:51:50,914 --> 00:51:52,665
-Which one should we watch?
-That's not what I meant.

693
00:51:53,320 --> 00:51:55,320
It's boring to re-watch
the ones we already seen.

694
00:51:55,984 --> 00:51:57,388
I want to watch a new movie...

695
00:51:57,703 --> 00:51:58,823
...that you starred in.

696
00:52:01,715 --> 00:52:05,586
Just listening to your voice
isn't good enough for me anymore.

697
00:52:10,779 --> 00:52:12,146
Will you do that for me?

698
00:52:17,258 --> 00:52:19,015
My Segye is so kind.

699
00:52:20,633 --> 00:52:21,761
You're so obedient.

700
00:53:24,509 --> 00:53:25,669
Sir...

701
00:53:25,956 --> 00:53:27,342
...I'm Yoo Woomi.

702
00:53:27,516 --> 00:53:29,165
I'm Yoo Woomi of World Entertainment.

703
00:53:29,433 --> 00:53:30,922
Don't you trust my instinct?

704
00:53:31,047 --> 00:53:35,623
You've proven that you have good instinct
through Han Segye.

705
00:53:36,134 --> 00:53:38,408
But this is a huge project.

706
00:53:38,980 --> 00:53:41,387
We can't just cast any actors.

707
00:53:41,487 --> 00:53:45,353
Plus, the director requested
for an experienced actress.

708
00:53:45,596 --> 00:53:46,570
Exactly.

709
00:53:46,822 --> 00:53:49,091
That's why you should trust me.

710
00:53:50,113 --> 00:53:52,597
She must be quite the actress...

711
00:53:52,850 --> 00:53:54,672
...if you're talking so highly of her.

712
00:53:57,407 --> 00:53:59,650
Fine. Sure. Let's just go for her.

713
00:54:00,263 --> 00:54:01,520
Let's meet her.

714
00:54:01,978 --> 00:54:03,520
You will not regret this.

715
00:54:05,151 --> 00:54:06,933
I told her to be on time.

716
00:54:09,103 --> 00:54:10,359
Hi...

717
00:54:11,364 --> 00:54:12,847
Hello, sir.

718
00:54:14,494 --> 00:54:15,856
It's been a while.

719
00:54:15,941 --> 00:54:17,173
What do you think?

720
00:54:17,799 --> 00:54:20,375
She's a very experienced actress.

721
00:54:24,072 --> 00:54:25,325
Let's sign the contract.

722
00:54:26,401 --> 00:54:27,569
Right now.

723
00:54:58,571 --> 00:54:59,423
Cut!

724
00:54:59,698 --> 00:55:00,578
Okay.

725
00:55:04,081 --> 00:55:05,326
You did well.

726
00:55:05,410 --> 00:55:07,926
-How did I do?
-Is that even a question?

727
00:55:08,010 --> 00:55:09,827
You did so well,

728
00:55:10,083 --> 00:55:11,990
Actress Han.

729
00:55:12,180 --> 00:55:15,921
You have no idea how much I missed this.

730
00:55:16,006 --> 00:55:18,477
She can retire and come
back as she pleases.

731
00:55:18,562 --> 00:55:21,012
It must be nice to be able to do that.

732
00:55:21,172 --> 00:55:23,093
Why did she even retire
in the first place?

733
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:24,908
It was such a short break.

734
00:55:25,098 --> 00:55:25,939
Those little...

735
00:55:26,024 --> 00:55:27,122
Excuse me.

736
00:55:28,171 --> 00:55:29,044
It's fine.

737
00:55:44,045 --> 00:55:45,289
What can I do?

738
00:55:45,421 --> 00:55:46,742
I deserve it.

739
00:55:47,116 --> 00:55:49,436
I should take responsibility
for my actions.

740
00:55:51,138 --> 00:55:52,368
Han Segye.

741
00:55:53,836 --> 00:55:55,003
Let's wrap up for today.

742
00:55:55,088 --> 00:55:56,046
Already?

743
00:55:56,131 --> 00:55:58,604
What do you mean?
We get to finish early thanks to you.

744
00:55:58,707 --> 00:55:59,614
Also...

745
00:55:59,973 --> 00:56:00,840
...over there...

746
00:56:01,384 --> 00:56:02,660
...your boyfriend came.

747
00:56:03,139 --> 00:56:04,020
What?

748
00:56:12,069 --> 00:56:15,225
Your "Uncle" is one strange man.

749
00:56:15,510 --> 00:56:17,198
If he follows you around longer,

750
00:56:17,283 --> 00:56:18,853
his company will go under.

751
00:56:23,046 --> 00:56:24,785
-What is this?
-Your contract.

752
00:56:28,316 --> 00:56:30,095
(Spokesmodel Contract)

753
00:56:32,574 --> 00:56:34,649
I'm giving you this offer
as the CEO of the company.

754
00:56:35,501 --> 00:56:36,859
Let's sign the contract.

755
00:56:37,268 --> 00:56:38,500
Be T'road Airline's spokesmodel.

756
00:56:38,585 --> 00:56:41,001
You should give this to Woomi, not me.

757
00:56:41,086 --> 00:56:42,956
She's kind of uptight.

758
00:56:43,377 --> 00:56:45,607
She refused to even look at it
even though we know each other.

759
00:56:46,479 --> 00:56:48,037
I need my girlfriend's help.

760
00:56:48,517 --> 00:56:50,747
Put in a good word for me.

761
00:56:50,920 --> 00:56:52,365
Is this a solicitation?

762
00:56:52,450 --> 00:56:54,320
If it were, are you going to report me?

763
00:56:55,826 --> 00:56:56,867
Do you have a pen?

764
00:56:59,195 --> 00:57:00,067
Here.

765
00:57:01,950 --> 00:57:02,946
(CEO, Seo Dojae)

766
00:57:04,038 --> 00:57:05,497
(Han Segye)

767
00:57:09,598 --> 00:57:10,666
Mr. Sponsor,

768
00:57:11,038 --> 00:57:13,209
I'll do my utmost best to please you.

769
00:57:14,610 --> 00:57:16,070
What did I say?

770
00:57:16,757 --> 00:57:20,157
Haven't I told you to read the contract
carefully before you sign it?

771
00:57:20,519 --> 00:57:21,456
What?

772
00:57:24,914 --> 00:57:28,257
The employee must accompany the employer
on business trips upon request.

773
00:57:28,342 --> 00:57:32,799
While accompanying,
the employee must wear a red dress.

774
00:57:32,884 --> 00:57:34,824
Again? When?

775
00:57:35,045 --> 00:57:36,705
Well, whenever.

776
00:57:37,561 --> 00:57:39,115
When does the shooting end?

777
00:57:39,200 --> 00:57:41,152
Why are you still obsessed
over red dresses?

778
00:57:41,237 --> 00:57:42,976
There's no need for that anymore.

779
00:57:43,437 --> 00:57:44,766
The truth is,

780
00:57:45,450 --> 00:57:48,050
my ideal type of women
is those who wear red dresses.

781
00:57:48,610 --> 00:57:51,260
You've got to be kidding.

782
00:57:52,276 --> 00:57:54,747
Your outfit today is close enough.

783
00:57:55,510 --> 00:57:56,866
This is pink.

784
00:57:56,950 --> 00:57:58,667
-Sure.
-It's pink.

785
00:57:58,751 --> 00:57:59,663
Sure.

786
00:59:33,817 --> 00:59:35,393
Look at that face.

787
00:59:38,510 --> 00:59:39,763
Or that face.

788
00:59:46,220 --> 00:59:47,831
I could turn into either of them.

789
00:59:49,934 --> 00:59:51,833
Will you still want to be with me?

790
00:59:52,987 --> 00:59:54,558
We've already talked about this.

791
00:59:55,831 --> 00:59:57,011
Bet your life...

792
00:59:57,421 --> 00:59:58,369
...on me.

793
01:00:27,473 --> 01:00:30,067
(Beauty Inside)

794
01:00:30,152 --> 01:00:32,188
Come out. Let's go on a date.

795
01:00:32,273 --> 01:00:34,034
Mr. Han Segye's Boyfriend.

796
01:00:34,244 --> 01:00:35,560
I'll call you when I'm done.

797
01:00:35,645 --> 01:00:37,124
Or not.

798
01:00:38,333 --> 01:00:39,909
He's so considerate of me.

799
01:00:39,994 --> 01:00:42,296
He calls me immediately
once he gets off work.

800
01:00:42,381 --> 01:00:44,939
Are you bragging in front of me?

801
01:00:45,024 --> 01:00:46,524
Do you have a boyfriend?

802
01:00:46,980 --> 01:00:48,004
She does.

803
01:00:48,394 --> 01:00:50,965
So now...

804
01:00:51,562 --> 01:00:52,454
...love me...

805
01:00:52,830 --> 01:00:55,342
...and yourself.
